summary: The video shows a makeup artist applying makeup to a woman. The artist applies primer, eyeshadow, eyeliner, and mascara to the woman's eyes. The video ends with the woman looking at the camera.

summary: The video shows a person spearfishing in South Florida. The creator is shown underwater in a wetsuit and mask, explaining the importance of hiding behind rocks or coral when hunting. They observe a school of fish, but note that parrotfish are protected and cannot be speared. The creator then spots a hogfish and describes it as delicious, with a minimum size requirement of 16 inches. The hogfish camouflages itself and swims away.
transcript: Catching my food. Whenever you're hunting, you want to make sure that you're hiding behind any rock or coral so that the fish that you want to eat doesn't see you. I looked onto a large parrot fish and while these guys do look big and tasty, you're not allowed to spear them because they're protected here in Florida. As I was following it, I ran out of air, so I decided to swim to the top. And from the top of the water, I saw a massive school of fish. Sometimes there's something tasty hiding in the school, so I went down to take a closer look. But when I didn't find anything, I waved them off and continued my search for what could be my breakfast. I stumbled across the most delicious fish in the sea, which is a lionfish. And when I took aim, I needed to make sure that I hit it good because these guys are destroying South Florida. That one fish wasn't going to be enough to feed me though, so I had to be extra stealthy. As I went across the bottom of the sea floor, looking for what else I can eat. I swam up to this hogfish that thought it was completely camouflaged. And when it realized that I saw it, it turned its camouflage off and slowly started swimming away. Well, this fish is delicious. It has to be a minimum of 16 inches, and this guy is just a little too small.

summary: The video demonstrates how to make a beat using a keyboard and digital audio workstation software. The creator explains the process in three simple steps: starting with the drums, adding a bassline, and then a melody. They suggest using a basic drum kit with a kick, snare, and hi-hat, and offer advice on creating a simple yet groovy bassline using a synth bass preset. For the melody, they recommend using a piano or synth and sticking to three or four notes. The video concludes with the creator encouraging viewers to make their own beat, post it, and tag them.
